1
00:00:00,864 --> 00:00:04,951
Invited by Sonoko, Kyogoku
visited the Suzuki residence...

2
00:00:06,828 --> 00:00:09,831
but ended up being disliked
by Sonoko's mother, Tomoko.

3
00:00:10,874 --> 00:00:14,878
And then, seeing Sonoko
get all excited about Kaito Kid...

4
00:00:16,171 --> 00:00:17,380
Lord Kid.

5
00:00:18,048 --> 00:00:19,257
What is it?

6
00:00:19,341 --> 00:00:21,676
Ad... Advisor.

7
00:00:24,095 --> 00:00:26,931
My name is Kyogoku Makoto.
I am a humble young man...

8
00:00:27,015 --> 00:00:30,226
who has the honor
of dating Miss Sonoko.

9
00:00:30,310 --> 00:00:33,897
Well, well, well.
So you're Sonoko's boyfriend.

10
00:00:34,564 --> 00:00:36,691
And what brings you here?

11
00:00:36,775 --> 00:00:39,027
I've heard that you possess
the jewel...

12
00:00:39,110 --> 00:00:41,863
that kaito kid is after.

13
00:00:42,238 --> 00:00:46,159
If that's the case, I humbly ask
that you allow me...

14
00:00:46,493 --> 00:00:49,245
to join the ranks
of your security detail.

15
00:00:49,329 --> 00:00:50,914
(phone ringing)

16
00:00:52,040 --> 00:00:57,170
What kind of man is he?
I hear he's a karateka, but...

17
00:00:57,253 --> 00:01:01,675
He's no ordinary karateka.
Four hundred world matches, undefeated.

18
00:01:01,758 --> 00:01:04,928
The unbeatable
Prince of Kicks.

19
00:01:06,554 --> 00:01:10,892
F... Four hundred and undefeated?

20
00:01:11,559 --> 00:01:16,314
Huh? Keep security out
of the jewel exhibit room?

21
00:01:16,773 --> 00:01:19,901
Kaito Kid is coming to steal it!

22
00:01:20,235 --> 00:01:23,321
He says they'd interfere with
the latest security system.

23
00:01:23,405 --> 00:01:26,616
Advisor Suzuki
just called me about it.

24
00:01:26,700 --> 00:01:28,243
Ugh...

25
00:01:28,702 --> 00:01:33,957
One man is surrounded
by guys aiming pistols at him.

26
00:01:34,708 --> 00:01:40,046
Sure, they're BB guns,
but at this range, with this many...

27
00:01:40,130 --> 00:01:42,507
And the man in the middle...

28
00:01:42,590 --> 00:01:46,761
is wearing a gas mask
that blocks his vision.

29
00:01:47,345 --> 00:01:49,889
You'd think there's no way
he could dodge them all, right?

30
00:01:52,517 --> 00:01:54,686
(gunshots)

31
00:01:58,314 --> 00:02:02,485
Apparently he's the world's
strongest security system.

32
00:02:03,069 --> 00:02:05,822
But Tomoko to Kyogoku...

33
00:02:06,573 --> 00:02:08,032
and Kid to Sonoko...

34
00:02:09,075 --> 00:02:12,370
had each proposed
a certain wager.

35
00:02:15,123 --> 00:02:16,791
Sun blazing down,
shrugging off the heat,

36
00:02:16,875 --> 00:02:18,501
a slick and stylish
deduction show.

37
00:02:18,585 --> 00:02:21,838
Kaito Kid's surprise scheme...
where will the security battle lead?

38
00:02:22,172 --> 00:02:23,548
Seeing through
the one and only truth.

39
00:02:23,631 --> 00:02:25,467
Looks like a kid,
mind of an adult...

40
00:02:25,550 --> 00:02:28,011
His name is Detective Conan!

41
00:02:30,992 --> 00:02:36,331
♪~

42
00:04:04,377 --> 00:04:10,383
~♪

43
00:04:12,177 --> 00:04:17,677
"Thief Kid vs. Makoto Kyogoku (Part 2)".

44
00:04:17,849 --> 00:04:20,101
Do your best, Makoto.

45
00:04:20,185 --> 00:04:22,145
Ah... yes.

46
00:04:22,562 --> 00:04:23,730
I...

47
00:04:25,440 --> 00:04:26,733
I believe in you.

48
00:04:27,775 --> 00:04:30,278
Yes. I'll protect it,
no matter what.

49
00:04:30,987 --> 00:04:32,780
I stake these fists on it.

50
00:04:35,241 --> 00:04:36,951
Come on, Sonoko.

51
00:04:51,007 --> 00:04:54,344
I believe in you too.

52
00:04:54,719 --> 00:04:58,097
That you'll keep
that promise of yours.

53
00:04:59,849 --> 00:05:00,850
Yes.

54
00:05:03,269 --> 00:05:04,354
Of course.

55
00:05:05,355 --> 00:05:09,025
Good. I'll be looking
forward to it.

56
00:05:13,321 --> 00:05:16,032
Would you care to make
a wager with me?

57
00:05:16,950 --> 00:05:19,244
A wager, you say?

58
00:05:19,577 --> 00:05:24,624
Yes. If you manage to
protect the jewel splendidly,

59
00:05:24,707 --> 00:05:26,709
then I'll accept it
as fate...

60
00:05:26,793 --> 00:05:30,004
and approve of your
relationship with Sonoko.

61
00:05:30,296 --> 00:05:34,551
But if that fails, and you're
bested by that thief...

62
00:05:34,926 --> 00:05:38,096
then you'll give up
on Sonoko for good.

63
00:05:38,179 --> 00:05:39,681
Do we have a deal?

64
00:05:39,764 --> 00:05:40,765
Uh...

65
00:05:41,933 --> 00:05:45,270
(crowd) Kid! Kid! Kid! Kid!

66
00:05:45,353 --> 00:05:51,192
Kid! Kid! Kid!

67
00:06:00,201 --> 00:06:01,703
Kid! Kid!

68
00:06:01,786 --> 00:06:03,705
Kid! Kid!

69
00:06:04,205 --> 00:06:08,876
What? A letter from Kid
arrived at this museum?

70
00:06:09,377 --> 00:06:12,338
And it's addressed
to this man again?

71
00:06:12,422 --> 00:06:15,258
Y... Yes. About a hundred
of them, all at once.

72
00:06:15,341 --> 00:06:17,635
A... A hundred?

73
00:06:20,638 --> 00:06:23,391
Looks like invisible ink again.

74
00:06:23,975 --> 00:06:28,396
Hey, hey, we can't heat
a hundred letters one by one
with a lighter.

75
00:06:28,479 --> 00:06:30,565
Then could you prepare
a candle...

76
00:06:30,648 --> 00:06:32,525
and a candlestick for me?

77
00:06:33,026 --> 00:06:36,112
Heating them that way
should save us some trouble.

78
00:06:36,195 --> 00:06:37,572
Hmm.

79
00:06:37,655 --> 00:06:41,534
Hey, somebody bring
a candle and a candlestick!

80
00:06:45,955 --> 00:06:47,665
Wh... What is this?

81
00:06:48,291 --> 00:06:51,377
"The prey I target never escapes...
the world's greatest thief."

82
00:06:51,461 --> 00:06:54,255
"Nothing is impossible
for the magician under the moon."

83
00:06:54,339 --> 00:06:58,926
"The world's strongest security
system? That's hilarious."

84
00:06:59,010 --> 00:07:04,641
...None of these
say anything important.

85
00:07:06,601 --> 00:07:08,311
Step back, step back.

86
00:07:08,394 --> 00:07:10,605
Please move back a bit more.

87
00:07:11,856 --> 00:07:13,816
Don't come any closer.

88
00:07:14,651 --> 00:07:18,321
Heh heh. This isn't even
an exhibit anymore.

89
00:07:18,404 --> 00:07:19,906
Whoops.

90
00:07:20,740 --> 00:07:24,744
But what's the deal
with all these letters?

91
00:07:26,245 --> 00:07:29,916
To rattle Kyogoku, who's
guarding the jewel?

92
00:07:30,291 --> 00:07:31,501
Or maybe...

93
00:07:32,043 --> 00:07:32,460
(crowd) Kid! Kid! Kid!

94
00:07:32,460 --> 00:07:34,754
(crowd) Kid! Kid! Kid!
(announcement) It is now
closing time.

95
00:07:34,754 --> 00:07:34,837
(crowd) Kid! Kid! Kid!

96
00:07:34,837 --> 00:07:36,631
(crowd) Kid! Kid! Kid!
Thank you so much...

97
00:07:36,714 --> 00:07:41,260
for visiting us today.
We look forward to seeing you again.

98
00:07:41,761 --> 00:07:44,222
It is now closing time.

99
00:07:44,305 --> 00:07:47,600
Thank you so much
for visiting us today.

100
00:07:51,104 --> 00:07:52,855
Heh heh heh.

101
00:07:53,398 --> 00:07:56,943
Come whenever you like,
Kaito Kid.

102
00:07:57,026 --> 00:08:00,530
Today, I'll show you
what I'm made of.

103
00:08:02,240 --> 00:08:05,785
You will, that is.
Nwa ha ha ha ha!

104
00:08:06,119 --> 00:08:07,912
I've got a bad feeling.

105
00:08:09,163 --> 00:08:12,291
Like we're being neatly
played by him somehow...

106
00:08:12,375 --> 00:08:15,044
What's wrong, Conan-kun?

107
00:08:16,003 --> 00:08:17,672
You've got such a scary face on.

108
00:08:17,755 --> 00:08:20,091
Ran-neechan. Huh?

109
00:08:20,174 --> 00:08:23,052
Hee hee.
What do you think of this outfit?

110
00:08:23,136 --> 00:08:25,513
I picked the most modest one.

111
00:08:25,596 --> 00:08:27,473
It... It looks good on you.

112
00:08:28,433 --> 00:08:30,727
Really? I'm glad.

113
00:08:32,895 --> 00:08:33,980
Ah ha ha.

114
00:08:34,439 --> 00:08:37,525
M... Modest? The neckline's
way too open.

115
00:08:37,608 --> 00:08:38,609
Ah.

116
00:08:38,985 --> 00:08:40,778
Makoto.

117
00:08:40,862 --> 00:08:41,904
Hm?

118
00:08:42,405 --> 00:08:46,409
I'm wearing an outfit
like this, so don't forget it.

119
00:08:46,784 --> 00:08:49,620
Ah... no. Yes.

120
00:08:57,086 --> 00:09:00,882
Now then, five minutes
until the time on the notice.

121
00:09:00,965 --> 00:09:03,968
Everyone, please leave
this exhibit room.

122
00:09:06,512 --> 00:09:11,100
From here on, until this
is over, anyone who enters...

123
00:09:11,976 --> 00:09:14,061
will be regarded as an enemy...

124
00:09:14,562 --> 00:09:17,273
and subdued with everything
I have.

125
00:09:17,356 --> 00:09:18,566
Eh...?

126
00:09:18,649 --> 00:09:21,527
A... All right.
Understood.

127
00:09:25,531 --> 00:09:27,909
I'm counting on you
for the rest.

128
00:09:36,584 --> 00:09:41,923
All right, we won't let
a single soul into this room either!

129
00:09:42,006 --> 00:09:43,257
Yeah!

130
00:09:44,175 --> 00:09:46,552
Ah... I'm gonna hit
the bathroom real quick.

131
00:09:48,095 --> 00:09:49,472
Hey.

132
00:09:49,889 --> 00:09:53,309
Those are the letters
that came from Kid, right?

133
00:09:53,392 --> 00:09:54,477
Yeah.

134
00:09:54,560 --> 00:09:56,354
If there are that many...

135
00:09:56,437 --> 00:10:00,608
did someone from the post office
deliver them straight to
the museum office?

136
00:10:01,442 --> 00:10:03,569
Nah. Miss Sonoko...

137
00:10:03,653 --> 00:10:06,739
got them handed to her
directly by the mail carrier.

138
00:10:07,698 --> 00:10:09,116
Sonoko did?

139
00:10:09,700 --> 00:10:12,370
Was she wearing that outfit then?

140
00:10:12,662 --> 00:10:14,747
Good work out there.

141
00:10:15,331 --> 00:10:20,086
Yeah. She finished changing
first and stepped out to check
on things outside...

142
00:10:20,169 --> 00:10:23,256
and happened to run into
a mail carrier she knew.

143
00:10:27,635 --> 00:10:31,472
Let me see one of those letters.
I won't take it out of the bag.

144
00:10:31,556 --> 00:10:33,683
H... Hey.

145
00:10:34,225 --> 00:10:37,311
Just as I thought...
no reaction to the black light.

146
00:10:39,939 --> 00:10:43,150
...Which means, don't tell me,
Sonoko...

147
00:10:44,694 --> 00:10:45,778
A... A blackout?

148
00:10:55,872 --> 00:10:59,208
I'm sorry, Makoto.

149
00:11:09,716 --> 00:11:13,345
(crowd chanting "Kid")
(timer ticking)

150
00:11:13,428 --> 00:11:15,013
(time signal)

151
00:11:17,057 --> 00:11:18,933
A... A blackout?

152
00:11:20,685 --> 00:11:22,145
Something's glowing.

153
00:11:22,395 --> 00:11:24,397
And quite a lot of them, too.

154
00:11:25,690 --> 00:11:27,150
Fluorescent paint?

155
00:11:31,613 --> 00:11:34,783
Huh? Looks like something
rolled over here.

156
00:11:35,325 --> 00:11:37,535
Ah, this is bad.

157
00:11:37,619 --> 00:11:39,871
Ran-neechan, get away!

158
00:11:39,954 --> 00:11:42,332
Uwaah!

159
00:11:42,707 --> 00:11:43,833
Whoaa!

160
00:11:44,542 --> 00:11:47,712
Don't panic!
It's the usual knockout gas.

161
00:11:47,796 --> 00:11:50,090
As long as we've got
gas masks on, this is nothing...

162
00:11:53,760 --> 00:11:55,512
Oh...

163
00:11:58,056 --> 00:12:00,558
Ah... damn it.

164
00:12:03,019 --> 00:12:05,897
Whoa!

165
00:12:06,398 --> 00:12:08,483
Curse you, Kid... Oh...

166
00:12:11,653 --> 00:12:13,655
Kyaaah!

167
00:12:14,239 --> 00:12:16,908
Ah... that voice, it's Sonoko.

168
00:12:16,991 --> 00:12:21,538
(knocking on door)
Makoto, can I come in?

169
00:12:25,333 --> 00:12:26,334
Ah...

170
00:12:33,633 --> 00:12:37,679
Makoto.
Sonoko, what on earth happened?

171
00:12:37,762 --> 00:12:40,265
Kaito Kid suddenly
cut the power...

172
00:12:40,348 --> 00:12:43,518
and filled the whole place
with knockout gas.

173
00:12:43,601 --> 00:12:46,980
I had this gas mask that
a guard gave me, so...

174
00:12:47,063 --> 00:12:48,898
I managed not to
get knocked out, but...

175
00:12:49,649 --> 00:12:54,529
the other guards had their masks
knocked off by Kid's card gun...

176
00:12:54,612 --> 00:12:58,575
(everyone sleeping)

177
00:13:00,160 --> 00:13:01,327
What in the world...

178
00:13:01,494 --> 00:13:02,495
The gas masks...

179
00:13:02,579 --> 00:13:05,165
had something like fluorescent
paint on them, so...

180
00:13:05,248 --> 00:13:08,585
in the dark, Kid must have
used that glow as a guide...

181
00:13:08,960 --> 00:13:11,629
Then he must still be
nearby!

182
00:13:11,713 --> 00:13:12,797
No.

183
00:13:12,881 --> 00:13:15,300
I think he's already
escaped.

184
00:13:15,800 --> 00:13:19,554
Because before the blackout,
a card from Kid arrived...

185
00:13:19,637 --> 00:13:21,890
saying he'd already
"received the jewel."

186
00:13:21,973 --> 00:13:23,475
That's impossible.

187
00:13:23,558 --> 00:13:26,311
The jewel's been around
my neck this whole time...

188
00:13:26,978 --> 00:13:30,190
Anyway, let's check
in a bright place...

189
00:13:30,273 --> 00:13:32,817
whether that jewel
is the real thing.

190
00:13:36,237 --> 00:13:40,909
Hmm. The moonlight through
the skylight alone isn't enough
to tell.

191
00:13:40,992 --> 00:13:41,993
Then...

192
00:13:43,995 --> 00:13:46,498
By candlelight.
Oh, right.

193
00:13:46,581 --> 00:13:48,708
There was a candle
for the invisible ink.

194
00:13:51,628 --> 00:13:54,964
I'm pretty sure the real one
was green, right?

195
00:13:55,632 --> 00:14:00,220
Ah... red? It's glowing red.

196
00:14:00,637 --> 00:14:04,057
So Kid did swap it
with a fake after all.

197
00:14:04,140 --> 00:14:05,975
B... But...

198
00:14:06,059 --> 00:14:08,937
when, and how on earth?

199
00:14:10,271 --> 00:14:13,525
For now, this fake...

200
00:14:13,608 --> 00:14:16,778
I'll go hand over
to the inspector.

201
00:14:18,613 --> 00:14:19,697
Ah... yes.

202
00:14:20,240 --> 00:14:24,244
Makoto, please tend to
the guards who were knocked out.

203
00:14:26,663 --> 00:14:27,664
Hm?

204
00:14:28,498 --> 00:14:33,294
You... you're not Sonoko,
are you?

205
00:14:33,670 --> 00:14:35,755
Wh... What are you saying?

206
00:14:35,838 --> 00:14:40,093
I'm the real one.
It's the jewel that's the fake.

207
00:14:40,260 --> 00:14:42,303
The jewel is real.

208
00:14:42,971 --> 00:14:45,056
C... Conan-kun?

209
00:14:45,557 --> 00:14:47,559
Alexandrite...

210
00:14:47,642 --> 00:14:51,396
under strong sunlight
rich in the blue-green spectrum...

211
00:14:51,479 --> 00:14:55,942
or under the fluorescent lights
in this museum, looks dark green.

212
00:14:56,025 --> 00:15:01,114
But under incandescent light
or candlelight, rich in the red
spectrum...

213
00:15:01,197 --> 00:15:04,409
it turns a vivid red.
In other words...

214
00:15:04,826 --> 00:15:06,995
the reason for sending all those
pointless invisible-ink letters...

215
00:15:07,078 --> 00:15:09,581
in such huge numbers...

216
00:15:10,582 --> 00:15:14,586
was to get a candle
prepared here on the spot.

217
00:15:15,128 --> 00:15:16,337
And those letters...

218
00:15:16,421 --> 00:15:20,049
were things hidden in advance
somewhere in this museum...

219
00:15:20,133 --> 00:15:22,844
handed over while
disguised as Sonoko, right?

220
00:15:23,136 --> 00:15:26,431
If you carelessly went through
the post office and they got
heated somewhere...

221
00:15:26,514 --> 00:15:28,558
the invisible ink would
develop early.

222
00:15:28,933 --> 00:15:33,605
The proof is, the barcodes
the post office uses for sorting...

223
00:15:33,688 --> 00:15:36,399
weren't on any of the letters.

224
00:15:36,983 --> 00:15:40,528
Invisible ink that reacts
to black light, that is.

225
00:15:42,322 --> 00:15:44,490
So Kid stripped me
of my clothes...

226
00:15:44,574 --> 00:15:47,410
and used them
for his disguise?

227
00:15:47,493 --> 00:15:49,412
No.

228
00:15:50,204 --> 00:15:54,167
Sonoko took off her own clothes
and handed them to Kid.

229
00:15:55,043 --> 00:15:58,212
To make the wager
with Kid happen.

230
00:15:58,463 --> 00:16:00,340
A wager?
Tch.

231
00:16:01,215 --> 00:16:02,592
Yeah.

232
00:16:02,675 --> 00:16:06,763
Whether Kyogoku could
see through Kaito Kid...

233
00:16:07,930 --> 00:16:11,017
when he impersonated her.

234
00:16:19,108 --> 00:16:20,985
Tch, he dodged it.

235
00:16:21,319 --> 00:16:23,696
(crumbling)

236
00:16:27,825 --> 00:16:29,202
Ah, crap.

237
00:16:34,999 --> 00:16:37,919
Where is he?
Where'd he go?

238
00:16:38,294 --> 00:16:40,254
Ha!

239
00:16:44,050 --> 00:16:47,428
Ha ha ha!

240
00:16:48,721 --> 00:16:50,932
I've claimed
the Green Emperor.

241
00:16:54,185 --> 00:16:55,186
Tch.

242
00:16:55,728 --> 00:17:00,274
Well, curse your own
incompetence at not being able
to fly...

243
00:17:01,234 --> 00:17:04,195
Mr. World's Strongest
Security System.

244
00:17:04,570 --> 00:17:05,780
You bastard...

245
00:17:11,828 --> 00:17:13,246
Get back.
Eh?

246
00:17:13,996 --> 00:17:14,997
Eh?

247
00:17:17,542 --> 00:17:18,543
Hmph!

248
00:17:19,544 --> 00:17:20,712
Hyah!

249
00:17:21,587 --> 00:17:23,256
Huh?

250
00:17:24,006 --> 00:17:26,300
He split a pillar with karate?

251
00:17:26,384 --> 00:17:30,304
N... No way. Is he planning
to break the pillars and bring
the ceiling down?

252
00:17:30,388 --> 00:17:32,890
(guards sleeping)

253
00:17:32,974 --> 00:17:35,518
Scary. I'd better
get out of here fast.

254
00:17:36,436 --> 00:17:38,062
Haa!

255
00:17:40,732 --> 00:17:41,733
Ah...

256
00:17:48,281 --> 00:17:49,282
Hmph.

257
00:17:49,949 --> 00:17:51,033
No way.

258
00:17:51,617 --> 00:17:53,327
Y... Yikes!

259
00:17:56,247 --> 00:17:58,291
H... He flew?

260
00:18:02,920 --> 00:18:05,882
A... As expected
of the world's strongest.

261
00:18:06,257 --> 00:18:09,510
Now, hand them back
to me, won't you?

262
00:18:10,678 --> 00:18:14,515
Both the jewel
and Sonoko's heart.

263
00:18:16,642 --> 00:18:22,565
Ah, since it wasn't what I was after,
I can return the jewel.

264
00:18:23,691 --> 00:18:25,943
But the young lady's heart,
that I can't.

265
00:18:26,277 --> 00:18:28,196
Wh... What?

266
00:18:30,823 --> 00:18:36,412
Heh. There's nothing to return,
since I never took it
in the first place.

267
00:18:36,788 --> 00:18:37,789
Ah...

268
00:18:40,124 --> 00:18:42,835
From the moment I proposed
this wager.

269
00:18:44,879 --> 00:18:48,591
F... Fine. I'll take you up
on that wager, but...

270
00:18:49,717 --> 00:18:52,178
don't injure him.

271
00:18:52,261 --> 00:18:56,390
Makoto's got a big tournament
coming up next week.

272
00:18:57,683 --> 00:18:59,560
W... Who's there?

273
00:19:00,269 --> 00:19:02,480
K... Kaito Kid?

274
00:19:03,439 --> 00:19:06,859
Good grief. It seems
I can't keep the fact...

275
00:19:06,943 --> 00:19:11,447
that I was here a secret,
so tell your friends a suitable lie.

276
00:19:11,531 --> 00:19:14,450
Especially that boy
with the glasses.

277
00:19:19,664 --> 00:19:21,457
But... well, unfortunately...

278
00:19:22,208 --> 00:19:25,127
it seems I did let him take
a small injury or two.

279
00:19:27,922 --> 00:19:30,007
The wager is completely...

280
00:19:36,556 --> 00:19:38,558
your win, young lady.

281
00:19:42,353 --> 00:19:43,354
Heh.

282
00:19:52,071 --> 00:19:58,077
♪~

283
00:21:06,270 --> 00:21:11,567
~♪

284
00:21:12,652 --> 00:21:13,861
What?

285
00:21:14,236 --> 00:21:18,115
You were stripped of everything
and locked in the bathroom?

286
00:21:18,741 --> 00:21:20,076
Is that true, Sonoko?

287
00:21:20,159 --> 00:21:21,786
Y... Yeah, well.

288
00:21:21,869 --> 00:21:24,121
He shows no mercy,
even to a woman.

289
00:21:24,872 --> 00:21:28,209
Hmph. Kid told you
to say that, didn't he?

290
00:21:28,292 --> 00:21:30,127
So you wouldn't be
an accomplice.

291
00:21:30,378 --> 00:21:34,590
Then don't tell me, the one who put
fluorescent paint on the gas masks...

292
00:21:34,674 --> 00:21:36,717
Good work out there.

293
00:21:36,801 --> 00:21:40,471
Ugh...

294
00:21:40,554 --> 00:21:41,722
was back then.

295
00:21:42,348 --> 00:21:45,101
Damn that Kid.

296
00:21:47,395 --> 00:21:52,358
Still, you did a fine job
protecting the treasure.

297
00:21:52,441 --> 00:21:56,487
No. In the end,
I let Kid get away.

298
00:21:56,862 --> 00:21:57,947
My apologies.

299
00:21:58,447 --> 00:22:00,658
No, no, it's fine.

300
00:22:00,741 --> 00:22:03,035
The contest is carried over
to next time.

301
00:22:03,119 --> 00:22:04,704
And next time...

302
00:22:04,787 --> 00:22:07,248
Yes. Next time, without fail.

303
00:22:07,665 --> 00:22:09,250
Well said.

304
00:22:09,333 --> 00:22:12,461
That's the world's strongest
security system for you.

305
00:22:12,545 --> 00:22:14,755
Gah ha ha ha!

306
00:22:15,297 --> 00:22:18,426
He's quite a reliable
young man, isn't he?

307
00:22:18,718 --> 00:22:22,930
Yes. Earnest, plainspoken...

308
00:22:23,014 --> 00:22:25,766
polite, and a tough,
sturdy man.

309
00:22:25,850 --> 00:22:28,811
Heh heh.
He'll be such fun to torment.

310
00:22:29,437 --> 00:22:30,521
Scary.

311
00:22:31,731 --> 00:22:35,526
Sorry, Makoto.
For pulling a stunt to test you.

312
00:22:35,609 --> 00:22:38,529
Ah... no.
So anyway...

313
00:22:39,030 --> 00:22:40,906
when did you figure it out?

314
00:22:40,990 --> 00:22:43,951
That that was Kid in disguise.
Eh?

315
00:22:44,452 --> 00:22:47,496
Was it because I'm
prettier, maybe?

316
00:22:47,580 --> 00:22:50,207
Hey, hey, it was, right?

317
00:22:50,583 --> 00:22:52,752
Ah... no.

318
00:22:53,919 --> 00:22:56,338
Actually...
Hm?

319
00:23:00,259 --> 00:23:01,677
Ehh?

320
00:23:01,761 --> 00:23:06,348
Unlike me, Kid's ring finger
was longer than his index finger?

321
00:23:07,349 --> 00:23:09,393
You seriously figured it out
from that?

322
00:23:09,852 --> 00:23:10,895
Yes.

323
00:23:10,978 --> 00:23:15,941
I've gotten into the habit of instantly
spotting an opponent's physical traits.

324
00:23:16,025 --> 00:23:18,235
Wasn't there anything else?

325
00:23:18,319 --> 00:23:21,530
Like how I had a more
pure vibe or something.

326
00:23:21,614 --> 00:23:23,491
P... Pure?

327
00:23:23,574 --> 00:23:27,661
You know, innocent,
unsullied, that kind of thing.

328
00:23:27,745 --> 00:23:30,164
Hmm.
You're hesitating!

329
00:23:30,247 --> 00:23:33,042
S... Sorry.
Oh, come on.

330
00:23:33,667 --> 00:23:38,964
Well, due to hormones, women's
index fingers tend to be longer
than their ring fingers...

331
00:23:39,048 --> 00:23:41,801
and for men it's the opposite,
so they say.

332
00:23:42,551 --> 00:23:45,179
There are quite a few
exceptions, though.

333
00:23:46,180 --> 00:23:49,350
Ah, my ring finger's long!
Heh heh.

334
00:23:52,436 --> 00:23:54,522
Was there some kind
of accident over there?

335
00:23:55,523 --> 00:23:57,358
If so, those flowers...

336
00:23:58,275 --> 00:23:59,527
It's gone.

337
00:23:59,985 --> 00:24:01,946
That thing is.
Eh...?

338
00:24:02,029 --> 00:24:03,864
Gone? Don't tell me...

339
00:24:06,784 --> 00:24:08,869
That smell from earlier,
just as I thought.

340
00:24:10,496 --> 00:24:12,832
It's embarrassing,
so don't tell anyone.

341
00:24:13,124 --> 00:24:14,834
Ah... yes. Of course.

342
00:24:15,485 --> 00:24:17,085
Next Conan,

343
00:24:17,085 --> 00:24:20,985
"Detective Love Story at MPD Headquarters (Confession)".

344
00:24:36,385 --> 00:24:39,185
Next Conan's Hint:

345
00:24:39,185 --> 00:24:41,285
"Masked Yaiba".

346
00:24:41,285 --> 00:24:42,585
Boy, that was close!

347
00:24:42,585 --> 00:24:44,185
There's another master of Karate.
348
00:24:44,185 --> 00:24:46,185
I know her really well.
